narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned about the history of different writing hands, about the processes of manuscript production, and cultivated my paleography skills reading different scripts nearly each week.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The biggest strength of this course is that we got to work with and examine authentic examples each week from Yale's collection of what we were studying. I also found a very interesting make-up of students in the class. I think a weakness of this course was how the assignments reflected only a small part of what we were studying and also the expectations that were given for them were at times not entirely clear.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would! When else will you have the chance to study properties of manuscripts alongside the actual objects?! So cool!
